que after years of teaching friction fires and I have to say that it's the easiest method I've ever used personally. I cut a lot out in order to make this less than a minute but from start of friction application to flame was under a minute. I've gotten 48 second flames from bow drill before but it was MUCH more effort. I hope you guys enjoy!

Most Viral Edit: Thank you so much for being interested in this one!!! I really enjoyed making this and if you are interested in seeing more of my stuff please check out our channel: https://www.youtube.com/followthecompassnorth

There will be a hand made (by me) Damascus (layered steel) knife giveaway this summer and I answer every question on every YT video so you can consider me your own personal survival resource!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/jLvW0cr</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[LiberalViking]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Love this...hope it catches on</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/HBSY57n</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/DYcWx20.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9Pv9lBo.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/G38s0hf.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/gpNNIMm.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/0iW8PL1.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NuSH7BS.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/denver-star-program-expands-in-2022/</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/HBSY57n</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[nosushi4me]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>It’s the little things</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/TlbHsap</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/sJQNYaa.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/TlbHsap</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ZUXUX]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>It's the little things that count.....</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/jYkuzCT</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9aEV22n.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/jYkuzCT</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MissDeeMeanor]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Wrong side of history</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/xEMh75R</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Cx0XMRX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/xEMh75R</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[angelinesg7]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Price gouging</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/n2NSEsC</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/XufvEv5.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>$4.11 is about $5.22 in 2022 dollars.  I am seeing gas at $4.30 in my neighborhood. California current avg, regular = $5.740, premium = $6.068, diesel = $6.290 (from the comments)</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/n2NSEsC</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[yokwe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I’m one of the burn pit veterans</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/WE9z2E4</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ufGD5kx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Yhhra4q.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>As a Marine Corps veteran who was directly exposed on two of my deployments, this disgusts me. My first deployment  (2008) we had to burn our own pit only 75yds from our living area for trash and human waste, as in I was part of working parties that lit our own pits. On my second deployment (2010-2011) we were only 100yds away. I struggle with constant sinusitis, breathing issues, and it just keeps getting worse.

How can this be a partisan issue? How is this even a question of support? These are rhetorical questions, I know why. But still, I don't understand how someone can look at themselves in the mirror every morning and feel good about voting against. 

